                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id = "a1">
                        <locus target = "#ir"></locus>Genealogy of the early Shoan dynasty,  in Amharic in a crude ‎hand.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a2">
                        ‎<locus target = "#iv"/>
                        <title>The story of the sorcerer at the Sea of Tiberias.</title> ‎
                        <desc>With incipit: <foreign xml:lang = "amh">በስመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ አፍጠለሹም፡ ፫ጊዜ፡ ያሸብክ፡ ጸሎተ፡ ንድራ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ወእንዘ፡ የሐውርል እግዚእነ፡ ውስተ፡ ባሕረ፡ ጥብርያዶስ፡ ...</foreign>‎</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a3">
                        <locus target ="#iir"/> List of names in a crude hand.
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a4">
                        <desc type = "GuestText">
                          <locus from = "#iiv" to ="#ivv"/>
                        Excerpt from <title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2444Temher"/><foreign xml:lang = "gez">ፍትሐ፡ ወዘእምታን፡ (sic) ተንስአ፡...</foreign>
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a5">
                        <locus target = "#178v"/>: Settlement of an unidentifiable dispute.
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e6">
                        Quire nine (<locus target = "#109r"/>) and ten (<locus target = "#123r"/>) are both numbered as quire ‎nine making numbers on subsequent quires off by one.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a6">
                        ‎In a later hand, directory for reading: Psalm 3 for all occasions, <locus target = "#2r"/>;
                        Psalm ‎‎6 in time of plague, <locus target = "#3v"/>;
                        Psalm 29 when seeing a dream, <locus target = "#22v"/>;
                        Psalm 32 ‎for help in falling in love, <locus target = "#25v"/>;
                        read Psalm 50 with Psalm 41, <locus target = "#44r"/>;
                        Psalm 51 ‎against the enemy, <locus target = "#44v"/>; (the directory on <locus target = "#47r #49r"/>, not ‎clear)
                        Psalm 127 when something bad happens to you, <locus target = "#122r"/>;
                        fifth ‎part of the Song of Songs for meal (“daily bread”? sisit), <locus target = "#159r"/>.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a7">
                        The same later hand arranges the codex for the days of the week
                        Monday, <locus target = "#1r"/>; Tuesday, <locus target = "#25r"/>; Wednesday, <locus target = "#51r"/>;
                        Thursday, <locus target = "#74v"/>; Friday, <locus target = "#105v"/>; Saturday, <locus target = "#122v"/>; Sunday, <locus target = "#137r #151v"/>.)
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a8">
                        <desc type = "OwnershipNote"> Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ተስፋው፡ ባዩህ፡</foreign> <locus target = "#61r"/>
                        <locus target ="#61v"/>.
                        Other names: <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ወልደ፡ ጸድቅ፡ አየነው፡</foreign>
                        <locus target = "#177v #178r"/>,
                        and <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ጋብራ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ አሠብር፡</foreign> (?),
                        <locus target = "#178r"/>.
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e7">
                        Columetric layout of text: <locus target = "#133v"/> (Ps. 145, name of God alternates between red and black from one line to the next),
                        <locus from = "#134v" to = "#135r"/> (Ps. 148), <locus target = "#136r"/> (Ps. 150), <locus target ="#147r" to ="#147v"/> (tenth biblical canticle).
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id = "e8">
                    Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#35v #62r #174v"/>);
                    and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#81r"/>).
                  </item>
